signature_matches.description: Found a high number of Window / User specific system calls (may be a loop to detect user behavior)
PE file has an executable .text section and no other executable section
Parts of this applications are using the .NET runtime (Probably coded in C#)
Sample monitors window changes (e.g. starting applications), analyze the sample with the 'Simulates keyboard and window changes' cookbook
Queries the volume information (name, serial number etc) of a device
Sample file is different than original file name gathered from version info
Contains modern PE file flags such as dynamic base (ASLR) or NX
Allocates memory with a write watch (potentially for evading sandboxes)
May sleep (evasive loops) to hinder dynamic analysis
URLs found in memory or binary data
Sample execution stops while process was sleeping (likely an evasion)
Sample might require command line arguments
PE file contains a COM descriptor data directory
Sample tries to load a library which is not present or installed on the analysis machine, adding the library might reveal more behavior

Sample may offer command line options, please run it with the 'Execute binary with arguments' cookbook (it's possible that the command line switches require additional characters like: "-", "/", "--")
May try to detect the virtual machine to hinder analysis (VM artifact strings found in memory)
Creates guard pages, often used to prevent reverse engineering and debugging
match_data: page read and write | page guard
